    #whatisit
      .container
        %h1.main-title
          %span What is PGP ?

        .main-description
          %p PGP is a computer program that helps you keeping your privacy...
          %p Well, private.

        .main-uses
          %ul
            %li
              %h2 Encryption
              %p Using military-class algorithms, your files and communications will be readable only by the person that you want to.

            %li
              %h2 Signature
              %p Just like handwritten signature, digital signature proves that only the emitter could have sent this. It strenghten trust.

    #whyuseit
      .container
        %h1.main-title
          %span Why use it ?

        %ol.reasons
          %li
            %h2 Private
            %p Simply because privacy matters. Internet is a wonderful tool to communicate, it's also very easy to get spied on by curious friends, neighbours or governements.
          %li
            %h2 Simple
            %p Don't change your habits, your emails or your contacts. The only difference is that if you and someone else use PGP, your conversation will stay private.

          %li
            %h2 Free
            %p PGP is free as in free beer and free speech. You don't have to pay anything and the protocol specifications are open and tested by a worldwide community.

    #howto
      .container
        %h1.main-title
          %span How to use it ?

        %nav.select-usage
          For
          %ul
            %li.selected{data: {usage: "emails"}} emails
            %li{data: {usage: "chat"}} chat
            %li{data: {usage: "calls"}} calls
            %li{data: {usage: "file"}} files
            %li{data: {usage: "device"}} devices

        %nav.select-platform
          On
          %ul
            %li.selected{data: {platform: "windows"}} Windows
            %li{data: {platform: "macos"}} MacOS
            %li{data: {platform: "linux"}} Linux
            %li{data: {platform: "iphone"}} iPhone
            %li{data: {platform: "android"}} Android

        %ul.howtos
          %li{data: {usage: "emails", platform: "windows"}}
            Windows emails
          %li.not-available.hidden
            Not available yet

